I agree with Felath, it's how these kind of games work, I personally loved the Diablo series, but there the focus on items, and the power gained from those items was alot greater then in DAOC.<P>In DAOC the lvl is more important than the equipment wich wasn't true in Diablo.  If you had a high lvl character there with medium items you would die from a lower lvl char with superior items.  The main motivation for a player was getting the uber loot.<P>Anyway DiabloII is totaly hacked now and not too fun anymore, although I still play the game occasionally.<P>I like DAOC alot, and the Darkness Falls Dungeon is really great, at Bors all the realms get access to it on a regular base.<P>Before DF Hibernia dominated the scene, but now Midgard has all the relics ( prolly because the focus shifted from relics to DF )<P>Anyway with the addition of the BG's and DF most of the players have alot more fun, and that is what it's all about.<P>I agree one must invest alot of time in the game, but it is not impossible to get all the uber loot and also not necesary to be viable IMHO.<P>--------------------<P>Cyberwiz lvl 42 Briton Ice Wizard<BR>Tuffir lvl 13 Briton Mind/Body Sorcerer<BR>Bors<BR>Proud Defenders Of Arcadia member
